<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 26 at 8:58AM CDT  by NWS Norman-Oklahoma City</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern
Jefferson, southwestern Stephens and east central Cotton Counties
through 930 AM CDT...
At 857 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Hastings, moving northeast at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 40 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Waurika, Comanche, Hastings, Addington, Waurika Lake, and Empire
City.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
